show help and exit
    If no command names are provided, nuts help is displayed. Otherwise, Each command help is displayed.
    When Command is unknown or invalid, an error message is displayed.

##) SYNOPSIS:

    ```sh nuts help [<-options>]... <command-name>...```

#!include</net/thevpc/nuts/runtime/includes/standard-command.ntf>

##) EXAMPLES

    ```sh nuts help --help```
        show this help and exit

    ```sh nuts help update```
        show help for update internal command

    ```sh nuts -Zy -w test help --colors ```
        show NTF help

    ```sh nuts -ZSbkKy -w=test6 settings --help ```
        echo with NFT format
